title: Former Greens leader Jeanette Fitzsimmons dies
text:
Photo: Ngataonga Sound & Vision

Former Green Party co-leader Jeanette Fitzsimons has died suddenly, aged 75.

She was was an MP from 1996 to 2010 and the co-leader of the Green Party from 1995 to 2009 alongside the late Rod Donald.

Former Green MP, close friend and neighbour Catherine Delahunty pays tribute.
